# Local env for `wrangler dev` in workers/api. Copy to `.dev.vars` (done for
# you by `pnpm setup`); `.dev.vars` is gitignored and never committed.
# Keep in sync with `apiEnvSchema` in packages/core/src/env.ts and docs/secrets.md.

# Which environment this isolate believes it is in ("local" | "preview" | "prod").
ENVIRONMENT=local

# The local Hyperdrive->Postgres connection string does NOT go here — wrangler
# ignores it in .dev.vars. It lives in this directory's `.env` (see .env.example).

# Clerk credentials — optional until the real Clerk app is provisioned
# (docs/secrets.md § "Flipping on real Clerk keys"); uncomment and fill in
# real test-instance keys to exercise authenticated flows locally.
# CLERK_SECRET_KEY=sk_test_placeholder
# CLERK_PUBLISHABLE_KEY=pk_test_placeholder

# Networkless session-JWT verification (issue #68): PEM public key from the
# Clerk dashboard's API-keys page ("JWT verification key"). Multiline PEM in
# dotenv needs quotes with \n escapes.
# CLERK_JWKS_PUBLIC_KEY="-----BEGIN PUBLIC KEY-----\n...\n-----END PUBLIC KEY-----"

# Comma-separated dashboard origins checked against the token's azp claim;
# unset = azp not checked (fine for local dev).
# CLERK_AUTHORIZED_PARTIES=http://localhost:5173

# Svix signing secret for POST /webhooks/clerk (issue #60) — from the
# webhook endpoint in the Clerk dashboard (docs/clerk-setup.md covers local
# tunneling with cloudflared/ngrok).
# CLERK_WEBHOOK_SIGNING_SECRET=whsec_placeholder
# PII field-encryption keyring (issue #47) — dev-only values, safe to commit
# because they never protect real data. Generate real keys with
# `openssl rand -base64 32`. PII_ENCRYPTION_KEYS maps key version -> base64
# 32-byte AES key (highest version encrypts new writes; keep old versions
# while rows encrypted with them exist). PII_HASH_KEY is separate and must
# not be rotated casually — rotating it orphans every stored value_hash.
PII_ENCRYPTION_KEYS={"1":"JB0/YtR2n0wh265yN8SRYBs45Lp0yt7sE2m+Ty6LOaE="}
PII_HASH_KEY=JKTMICa0vU/Ori8626X0AqH4D+At4aJ3cPg5JQBKqwI=

# Google Business Profile OAuth (issue #118, Epic #7). Unset URL vars
# default to the real Google hosts (apiEnvSchema); for local dev point them
# at the fake GBP server (issue #130): `pnpm dev:fake-gbp` serves every
# Google host from one origin on port 8799. The client id/secret are
# placeholders — the fake ignores their values; real ones arrive with the
# GCP OAuth client (ADR 0002 Appendix C).
GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID=fake-local-client-id
GOOGLE_CLIENT_SECRET=fake-local-client-secret
# HMAC key for the signed OAuth state param — dev-only placeholder (the
# value below is itself valid base64 decoding to 33 bytes, chosen to read
# as the placeholder it is), safe to commit; generate real keys with
# `openssl rand -base64 32`.
GOOGLE_OAUTH_STATE_SECRET=devonlygoogleoauthstatesecretplaceholder7777
GOOGLE_OAUTH_AUTH_URL=http://localhost:8799/o/oauth2/v2/auth
GOOGLE_OAUTH_TOKEN_URL=http://localhost:8799/oauth/token
GOOGLE_OAUTH_REVOKE_URL=http://localhost:8799/oauth/revoke
# Where the callback redirects back to (defaults to the local dashboard).
# DASHBOARD_ORIGIN=http://localhost:5173
# Override only behind a rewriting proxy; normally derived per request.
# GOOGLE_OAUTH_REDIRECT_URL=http://localhost:8787/api/integrations/google/callback

# Data-plane base URLs for location discovery (#121) — the fake serves
# every Google host from one origin.
GOOGLE_ACCOUNT_MANAGEMENT_URL=http://localhost:8799
GOOGLE_BUSINESS_INFORMATION_URL=http://localhost:8799
# Future Epic #7 issues (#123/#156) add their data-plane base URLs the
# same way; until then these document the pattern:
# GOOGLE_MYBUSINESS_V4_BASE_URL=http://localhost:8799
